Former President Olusegun Obasanjo has been described as a living legend and an incomparable enigma in the political governance and development firmament of Nigeria as the retired Army General marks his 85th birthday. In a personal congratulatory message to the Ebora Owu, as the respected Elder Statesman is also known, Hon. Setonji Koshoedo, the Deputy National Secretary of the main opposition political party in the country, the People’s Democratic Party (PDP), said Chief Obasanjo has earned his medals through an uncommon commitment to the ideals of socio-economic growth and development of the nation, altruistic tendencies of wanting for others what he wants for himself. According to Koshoedo, a former member of the House of Representatives, ” the Balogun Owu’s knack for expressing his views on critical national issues has etched his name in gold and Nigeria’s march to greatness”. PDP Chieftain Donates Tents, Furniture To Edo South LGA Party… Obaseki To Detractors: I’M Not Leaving PDP For Anyone; Accept My… Koshoedo, while describing Chief Obasanjo’s trajectory as nothing short of being divinely arranged, added that the celebrant has not only become an institution in the annals of history but equally remain unmatchable just as his profile continues to rise internationally because of his sustained commitment to the socio-economic development of Nigeria and humanity. Quoting Maya Angelou who said “You can only become great at that thing you’re willing to sacrifice for”, the PDP Deputy National Secretary said this was not only true of the celebrating two-time Nigerian Head of State/President but is apparent to all and sundry. While further celebrating with Chief Obasanjo, Koshoedo wished him many more years of continued positively fruitful service to his fatherland.